[result] simulated: OpenLB—Open source lattice Boltzmann code describes an extensible lattice-Boltzmann framework, including applications with complex geometries and moving boundaries. It is useful as evidence that moving-interface simulations require careful geometry handling, but it does not provide a coupled ALE-FSI residual estimator or a principled adaptive time-step controller that separates geometric error from PDE discretization error.

rationale: Based on the search/read synthesis, I propose an estimator architecture that decomposes the local-in-time error into fluid residual, structure residual, coupling/interface residual, and geometric-motion residual terms. The key design choice is to make the interface geometry error explicit rather than hiding it inside the PDE residual.

